      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"Step2\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Step 2: Add users to Intune"
    },
    {
      "content": "Now that you have set up your account, you'll use either the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>New Users<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> wizard to add individual user accounts to <ph id=\"ph1\">[!INCLUDE[wit_nextref](../Token/wit_nextref_md.md)]</ph>, or the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Bulk add users<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> wizard to add users in bulk (see the instructions in this section).",
      "pos": [
        7740,
        8003
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Before you get started, it's important that you understand how Intune handles administrator accounts.",
      "pos": [
        8005,
        8106
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A tenant administrator  uses the account portal to add  users to the Microsoft Intune <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Users Group<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        8108,
        8210
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Adding users to the  <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Users Group<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> assigns Intune subscription licenses to users and is also how you make those users to show up in the Microsoft Intune administration console.",
      "pos": [
        8211,
        8389
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Administrator accounts for Intune aren't created in the account portal,  as regular user accounts are.",
      "pos": [
        8391,
        8493
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Instead, you  assign  either read-only access or full access administrative rights to users by using the administration console in the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Administration<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> workspace under <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Administration Management<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        8494,
        8694
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Service administrators that are assigned read-only access cannot change Intune settings, but they can view data and run reports.",
      "pos": [
        8695,
        8823
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Service administrators with full access have all available administrative rights.",
      "pos": [
        8824,
        8905
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can view tenant administrator information by using the Intune administration console, but you cannot create tenant administrators there.",
      "pos": [
        8907,
        9047
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "By default, the subscription owner becomes a tenant administrator for your Microsoft Intune service and has full access to both the Intune account portal and the Intune administration console.",
